<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JAN 94 / The Finance Bill: Setback predicted for many funds -
Unapproved pensions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SCHEHERAZADE DANESHKHU
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The finance bill appears to have dealt a blow to all unapproved pension
schemes known as Furbs (funded unapproved retirement benefit schemes), which
seek to invest funds tax-efficiently, either offshore or in tax exempt
assets, according to Mr John Mackay, senior tax partner of accountants Ernst
&amp; Young.
The November Budget aimed to tax benefit received from a Furbs not
previously taxed in the UK.
The Inland Revenue said it would stop such schemes where income and capital
gains were wholly or partly taxed - providing employees with a larger
tax-free lump sum on retirement.
</TEXT>
