</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Members of the Royal Yachting Association are to be recruited to help
Customs and Excise in anti-drugs operations by reporting suspicious vessels
at sea.
Other sailors, ferry companies and airlines have already agreed to take part
in monitoring isolated stretches of coast as part of the Anti-Drugs
Alliance.
