FT  12 JAN 94 / Ciampi ready to stay on as PM
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italy's prime minister Mr Carlo Azeglio Ciampi indicated yesterday he would
like to stay in office, despite today's parliamentary no-confidence vote
which could determine the fate of his fragile eight-month government, writes
Haig Simonian in Milan.
At the Nato summit in Brussels, Mr Ciampi underlined his commitment to
remain at a time of great change for Italy. President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro
is expected to dissolve parliament and announce the date of new elections
shortly. Mr Ciampi is likely to remain in office as caretaker premier,
however the vote turns out.
