<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JAN 94 / Zambia cabinet shake-up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LUSAKA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
President Frederick Chiluba shook up Zambia's cabinet yesterday after two
ministers resigned over allegations of drug trafficking, Reuter reports from
Lusaka. Mr Remmy Muthoosa was named to replace Foreign Affairs Minister
Vernon Mwaanga, who quit last week.
At the Ministry of Community Development and Social Services, Princess
Nakatindi Wina quit on Saturday, as did her husband, Simota Wina, national
assembly deputy speaker. All three denied the allegations. Mr Chitalu Sampa
replaced Mr Newstead Zimba as home affairs minister; Mr Dipak Patel became
commerce minister.
