<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Claudio Generali, chairman of Banca del Gottardo of Lugano, was hit in
the lungs by a pistol shot when an assailant burst into his office
yesterday, writes Ian Rodger in Zurich. Mr Generali, also a vice chairman of
the Association of Foreign Banks in Switzerland and a former finance
minister of the Italian-speaking canton of Ticino, had emergency surgery and
is not in danger.
Mr Walter Canepa, a semi-retired Gottardo manager responsible for looking
after the funds of several of the bank's wealthy private clients, is being
held in custody.
