<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexican stock prices opened sharply weaker and extended their fall after the
weekend saw the Chiapas uprising spread into the Mexico City valley.
By the close the IPC index was down 165.92, or 6.32 per cent, to 2,459.11,
the biggest one-day percentage fall since October 16, 1989, when the market
dropped 8.05 per cent.
Brazil, in contrast, saw a further rise of 3.9 per cent after a climb of 7.2
per cent on Friday, the latest gains coming in an extended rally based on
politico-economic hopes. The Bovespa index finished 1,899 higher at 49,539.
</TEXT>
