<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Landed teas met fair but less general demand, reports The Tea Brokers'
Association. Assams met selective competition with better medium teas 10 to
20p lower and plainer descriptions 5 to 10p easier where sold. Pekoe dusts
were a weak feature throughout. Brightest East Africans eased by 5 to 10p
and closed upto 20p lower. Medium and plainer sorts declined by 3 to 5p.
Dust grades met limited support at easier rates with many withdrawals.
Ceylons attracted fair demand but at easier rates. Offshore fair demand
although prices were often easier by 5 to 10p. Quotations: quality 170p/kg,
good medium 140p/kg, medium 103p/kg and low medium 92p/kg. The highest price
realised this week was 180p/kg for a Rwanda pf. 1.
