<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Kleinwort's EPIT trust raises Pounds 320m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Kleinwort Benson's European Privatisation Investment Trust has raised about
Pounds 320m from institutions during the pre-placement period, making it
likely to be the second largest UK investment trust launch ever, and the
largest trust in Kleinwort's stable.
The public offer period, which starts today and closes on February 2, could
take the fund up to a total of as much as Pounds 400m.
Kleinwort originally announced that the fund aimed to raise Pounds 40m.
The largest investment trust launch was the Mercury World Mining Trust last
November, raising a total of Pounds 426m.
The offer price for EPIT is 100p, with 50 per cent due immediately and the
remainder six months later, to allow staggered investment of the funds.
There will be one warrant attached to every five shares, and the minimum
investment is Pounds 2,000.
The trust will initially buy shares in companies privatised within the last
five years, following the principle that most efficiency gains are realised
within five years of privatisation. These will be sold, or money borrowed,
to participate in new privatisation issues as they come up.
Up to 20 per cent of the fund will be invested in former Warsaw pact
countries, and up to 20 per cent in the UK. But the main emphasis will be on
European Union member countries apart from the UK. France, Italy and Spain
all have large privatisation programmes planned.
Mercury Asset Management is launching a similar European privatisation
trust, but with a larger UK content.
Investment trusts provide a simple way for individuals to invest in
privatisations outside the UK as they avoid the need for foreign bank
accounts and currency exchange costs.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>European Privatisation Investment Trust.
</CO>
