<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / Observer: Sweet SA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Aren't new democracies a wonderful thing? Take South Africa, now racing
towards its April 27 general election. Not only do all South Africans get a
vote, but they can now bite the head off the politician of their choice.
Mister Sweet, an inventive Jo'burg company, is selling bags of 'Multi Party
Politics' sweeties under the slogan: 'All the politicians you can swallow]'
You can masticate a jaundiced-coloured F W de Klerk; gobble up a chocolate
Desmond Tutu; or swallow a pink Eugene Terreblanche.
And with what is either a genuflection towards deep political correctness,
or an irony which may escape most South African voters, all taste the same.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Mister Sweet.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>ZAZ  South Africa, Africa.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P2064 Candy and Other Confectionery Products.
