FT  11 JAN 94 / Treasury rules out model sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER MARSH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Treasury has decided against privatising its computer model used in
economic forecasting, after more than a year of feasibility discussions,
Peter Marsh writes.
The decision, announced yesterday, was greeted as 'disappointing but
understandable' by DRI, the US-owned economics consultancy which last April
declared its interest in running the model.
Some economists have criticised faults in the model as being partly
responsible for poor Treasury forecasts in recent years.
Few UK economic consultancies said they were interested in taking over the
model because the work might be too complex and not profitable enough. The
Treasury said its decision had followed a recommendation by KPMG Peat
Marwick, the consultancy.
