<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / Barclays union threatens action
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Barclays Group Staff Union, which has about 50,000 members, will decide soon
whether to take industrial action over the decision by Barclays Bank to cut
a further 3,000 jobs over the next two years. The decision will follow an
emergency meeting of the staff union's regional chairmen next week.
The Bifu banking union, which has about 12,000 members at the bank, said
industrial action was 'a real possibility'. The union is particularly
concerned that a much higher proportion of the job losses will come from
compulsory redundancies than in previous cuts.
Bifu also issued a warning that thousands of other job losses in the sector
were coming, with statements from two other financial institutions expected
this week.
The Barclays announcement takes the total of job losses in the bank's
five-year programme to 21,000 - 16 000 have already gone. Barclays said it
believed there was still some scope for voluntary redundancies. It would
resort to compulsory redundancies only 'when other avenues have been fully
explored'.
