<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / Arsonist jailed for fraud attempt
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A businessman who set fire to his hotel in an attempted Pounds 2m insurance
fraud was jailed for four years at Bristol crown court yesterday.
In December Mr Mohammed Parvaz, of Fishponds, Bristol, was convicted of
arson while being reckless as to whether life was endangered at the Waverley
Hotel, Redland, Bristol - one of three hotels he owned in Bristol providing
bed and breakfast accommodation for people on social security.
Investigators found that the fire had been deliberately started with petrol.
Mr Parvaz was seen leaving the hotel minutes before the outbreak.
