<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JAN 94 / 460,000 packs of cereal recalled
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NEIL BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Quaker Oats, the breakfast cereal maker, is recalling 460,000 packs of Sugar
Puffs and Quaker Puffed Wheat, with a retail value of about Pounds 800,000,
after 'rough grain husks' which could irritate the throat were found in some
packs, Neil Buckley writes.
About 5,000 packs are believed to be affected by the problem, thought to be
the result of a breakdown in the sieving process. The company said there was
no danger to children or adults.
'However, these irregular shaped husks, which have rough edges, could cause
some throat discomfort and irritation, and small children could cough or
regurgitate them,' said Dr Gerry Jewell, quality-control director.
Packets affected are Sugar Puffs with a best before date of 30/11/94 and
batch codes L52-L90 marked on the packet top, or best before 31/12/94, batch
codes L01-L42, or Puffed Wheat best before 31/12/94, batch codes L16-18 and
L37-39.
Customers with such packs are advised to destroy the contents and send the
packet top with their name and address for a replacement voucher to Quaker
Oats, Dept 2000, Snowden Drive, Winterhill, Milton Keynes MK6 1HQ.
