   By SIMON HOLBERTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Hong Kong government is to ask local lawmakers to approve an extra
HKDollars 1.7bn (Pounds 148m) to sustain the colony's airport project in the
absence of a comprehensive financial agreement with China.
The money is needed to push ahead with building necessary works for the
airport on Chek Lap Kok, an island off the northern shore of Lantau.
